The paper deals with reinforcement learning for autonomous robotic platforms, specifically in the context of collision avoidance. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses neural networks and dropout to process sensory inputs, indicating that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of cameras as sensors suggests that the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category may also be relevant. Finally, the paper deals with uncertainty and safety in the learning process, which could fall under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
